    "answer_id" : 28649270,
    "question_id" : 17431312,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>Dherik : I'm not sure about what you say, when you don't use fetch the result will be of type : <code>List&lt;Object[ ]&gt;</code> which means a list of Object tables and not a list of Employee. </p>\n\n<pre><code>Object[0] refers an Employee entity \nObject[1] refers a Departement entity \n</code></pre>\n\n<p>When you use fetch, there is just one select and the result is the list of Employee <code>List&lt;Employee&gt;</code> containing the list of departements. It overrides the lazy declaration of the entity. </p>\n"
